<Window xmlns="https://github.com/avaloniaui"
  xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
  x:Class="Zer0Talk.Views.PrivacyPolicyDialog"
  Width="700" Height="600" CanResize="False"
  Title="Privacy Policy"
  ExtendClientAreaToDecorationsHint="True"
  ExtendClientAreaChromeHints="NoChrome"
  ExtendClientAreaTitleBarHeightHint="32"
  WindowStartupLocation="CenterOwner">

  <Grid RowDefinitions="Auto,*,Auto">

    <!-- Drag bar / title bar -->
    <Border Grid.Row="0" Padding="6" BorderBrush="{DynamicResource App.Border}" BorderThickness="0 0 0 1"
            Background="{DynamicResource App.Background}" PointerPressed="DragBar_PointerPressed">
      <Grid ColumnDefinitions="*,Auto" VerticalAlignment="Center">
        <TextBlock Text="Privacy Policy" FontSize="15" FontWeight="SemiBold"/>
        <Button x:Name="TitleCloseButton" Grid.Column="1" Content="✕" Classes="icon-button" Click="TitleClose_Click"/>
      </Grid>
    </Border>

    <!-- Scrollable policy body -->
    <ScrollViewer Grid.Row="1" Background="{DynamicResource App.Background}" Padding="20,14">
      <StackPanel Spacing="4" MaxWidth="640">

        <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" Foreground="{DynamicResource App.ForegroundSecondary}" FontSize="12">
          Zer0Talk is a private, end-to-end encrypted peer-to-peer messaging application. This policy explains what data is handled by the application and how.
        </TextBlock>

        <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" FontWeight="SemiBold" FontSize="12" Margin="0,4,0,0">
          Zer0Talk collects no data. There is no server that knows who you are, who you talk to, or what you say.
        </TextBlock>

        <!-- 1. Data Storage -->
        <TextBlock FontWeight="SemiBold" FontSize="13" Margin="0,10,0,2">1. Data Storage</TextBlock>
        <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" FontSize="12">
          All data is stored locally on your device only. Your account, contacts, messages, and settings are
          encrypted files stored in your local app data folder. No data is uploaded to any cloud service or
          third-party server. Everything is encrypted at rest using XChaCha20-Poly1305 with Argon2id key
          derivation — nothing is stored in plaintext.
        </TextBlock>

        <!-- 2. Your Identity -->
        <TextBlock FontWeight="SemiBold" FontSize="13" Margin="0,10,0,2">2. Your Identity</TextBlock>
        <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" FontSize="12">
          Your identity is a keypair (Ed25519). Your unique ID is derived from your public key. No email address,
          phone number, or real name is required or registered with any authority. There is no central account
          registry. No one other than you holds your identity.
        </TextBlock>

        <!-- 3. Messaging -->
        <TextBlock FontWeight="SemiBold" FontSize="13" Margin="0,10,0,2">3. Messaging</TextBlock>
        <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" FontSize="12">
          All messages are end-to-end encrypted. Messages are encrypted before leaving your device and decrypted
          only on the recipient's device. Session keys are established via ECDH (P-256) — a shared secret known
          only to the two parties in the conversation. No message content, metadata, or delivery receipts are
          stored on any server.
        </TextBlock>

        <!-- 4. Blind Relays -->
        <TextBlock FontWeight="SemiBold" FontSize="13" Margin="0,10,0,2">4. Blind Relays</TextBlock>
        <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" FontSize="12">
          When a direct connection is not possible, Zer0Talk can route through a blind relay. These are not
          servers in the traditional sense — they do not serve content, store data, or have any knowledge of
          what they are forwarding. A blind relay only facilitates the initial TCP connection request and then
          forwards an opaque, encrypted byte stream between two peers. The relay sees only ciphertext, retains
          nothing (no logs, no session records, no metadata), and cannot participate in or observe the
          cryptographic handshake. All key exchange happens directly between the two clients. Blind relays can
          be self-hosted.
        </TextBlock>

        <!-- 5. No Telemetry -->
        <TextBlock FontWeight="SemiBold" FontSize="13" Margin="0,10,0,2">5. No Telemetry</TextBlock>
        <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" FontSize="12">
          Zer0Talk does not collect analytics, crash reports, usage statistics, or telemetry of any kind. No data
          is sent to the developer, any analytics platform, or any third party. Auto-update version checks query
          the GitHub Releases API, disclosing your IP address to GitHub's servers and subject to GitHub's privacy
          policy. No other identifying information is sent.
        </TextBlock>

        <!-- 6. Features Intentionally Absent -->
        <TextBlock FontWeight="SemiBold" FontSize="13" Margin="0,10,0,2">6. Features Intentionally Absent</TextBlock>
        <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" FontSize="12">
          File and image transfers are intentionally absent due to exploitation and reputation risk. AI-assist
          features are deferred until a sound privacy trust model is defined. Cloud message backup is not
          planned — it contradicts the zero-knowledge principle. Screen capture by third-party tools is opted out
          by default using the Windows Content Protection API.
        </TextBlock>

        <!-- 7. Data Deletion -->
        <TextBlock FontWeight="SemiBold" FontSize="13" Margin="0,10,0,2">7. Data Deletion</TextBlock>
        <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" FontSize="12">
          To delete your account securely, use Settings → Danger Zone → Delete Account. This process
          cryptographically wipes your keypair, identity, messages, and contacts. Manually deleting individual
          files is not a secure deletion method — it may leave recoverable data on disk and bypass the
          multi-pass secure erase performed by the in-app deletion process. The developer has no access to
          your data and cannot fulfil data deletion requests on your behalf.
        </TextBlock>

        <!-- 8. Legal -->
        <TextBlock FontWeight="SemiBold" FontSize="13" Margin="0,10,0,2">8. Legal Compliance</TextBlock>
        <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" FontSize="12">
          Zer0Talk operates without access to user data. The developer cannot comply with subpoenas or governmental
          requests for user data — there is nothing to produce. Users are solely responsible for complying with
          all applicable local, national, and international laws when using Zer0Talk.
        </TextBlock>

        <!-- Full policy link -->
        <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" FontSize="12" Foreground="{DynamicResource App.ForegroundSecondary}" Margin="0,12,0,2">
          The authoritative and most current version of this policy is maintained on GitHub:
        </TextBlock>
        <Button Content="View Full Policy on GitHub" Click="OpenGitHub_Click" HorizontalAlignment="Left" Margin="0,0,0,4"/>
        <TextBlock FontSize="11" Foreground="{DynamicResource App.ForegroundSecondary}" TextWrapping="Wrap" Margin="0,0,0,12">
          https://github.com/AnotherLaughingMan/Zer0Talk-Releases/blob/main/PRIVACY-POLICY.md
        </TextBlock>

      </StackPanel>
    </ScrollViewer>

    <!-- Footer: accept checkbox + Do Not Show Again + Close button -->
    <Border Grid.Row="2" Padding="16,10" BorderBrush="{DynamicResource App.Border}" BorderThickness="0 1 0 0"
            Background="{DynamicResource App.Background}">
      <Grid ColumnDefinitions="*,Auto">
        <StackPanel Spacing="6" VerticalAlignment="Center">
          <CheckBox x:Name="AcceptCheckBox"
                    Content="I have read and understand the Privacy Policy"
                    IsCheckedChanged="AcceptCheckBox_Changed"/>
          <CheckBox x:Name="DoNotShowCheckBox"
                    Content="Do not show this dialog again"
                    IsEnabled="False"/>
        </StackPanel>
        <Button x:Name="CloseButton" Grid.Column="1" Content="Close"
                VerticalAlignment="Bottom" IsEnabled="False" Click="Close_Click"/>
      </Grid>
    </Border>

  </Grid>
</Window>
